criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Definite diagnosed with chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension with the
             right-sided cathrization and pulmonary angiography;

          -  The computed tomography imaging implied that the location of the embolism could be
             reached with surgeries;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Beyond the age limit described above,or combined with other severe conditions such as
             severe organ dysfunction and considered contraindicated for surgical therapy by the
             cardiac surgeons;

          -  Without the consent by the patient or his/her families;

          -  Acute pulmonary embolism;

          -  Pulmonary sarcoma;

          -  Pulmonary arteritis;

          -  Combined with cardiogenic pulmonary hypertension or idiopathic pulmonary hypertension;
